8 An Act relating to motor vehicles; amending 47 O.S.
2021, Section 12-609, which relates to required
9 equipment for motorcycles; deleting limitation on the
height of motorcycle handlebars; and providing an
10 effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 12-609, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 12-609. A. In addition to other requirements
17 prescribed by this chapter, by federal law or by local ordinance,
18 all motorcycles, except when operated on actual trail rides
19 conducted outside of public roads and highways, shall be equipped
20 with:
21 1. Two rearview mirrors, containing a reflection surface of not
22 less than three (3) inches in diameter, mounted one on each side of
23 the motorcycle and positioned so as to enable the operator to
24 clearly view the roadway to the rear of the vehicle;
