1 2. A windshield of sufficient quality, size and thickness to
2 protect the operator from foreign objects, except that in lieu of
3 such windshield, the operator shall wear goggles or other protective
4 eyewear which meets American National Standards Institute (ANSI)
5 Standard Z87.1 and provides positive retention, or a face shield of
6 material and design to protect the operator from foreign objects;
7 3. A properly operating speedometer capable of registering at
8 least the maximum legal speed limit for that motorcycle;
9 4. A fender over each wheel. All fenders shall be of the type
10 provided by the manufacturer;
11 5. A horn which shall comply with the requirements of Section
12 12-401 of this title; and
13 6. A muffler or other effective noise-suppressing system which
14 shall comply with the requirements of Section 12-402 of this title.
15 B. No person under eighteen (18) years of age shall operate or
16 ride upon any motorcycle unless such person is properly wearing a
17 crash helmet of a type which complies with standards established by
18 49 C.F.R., Section 571.218.
19 C. Handlebars on motorcycles shall not be higher than eye level
20 of the operator.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
